#: software/templates/about_us.html:20
msgid ""
"wger is built on the principles of open source. Its code is publicly "
"available, developed by our community, ensuring transparency and giving you "
"control over your data (especially if self-hosting). The free hosted service "
"runs entirely on this open-source foundation. We believe powerful fitness "
"tools should be accessible to everyone."
